"the :ref:`Managing VM docs <user/advanced-topics/managing-vm-"
"kernels:using kernel installed in the vm>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vm-troubleshooting.rst:12
#: afcc2d89ae5747f3bdcb5adcfbb5e827
msgid ""
"In case of problems, you can access the VM console using ``qvm-console-"
"dispvm VMNAME`` in dom0, then access the GRUB menu. You need to call it "
"just after starting the VM (until ``GRUB_TIMEOUT`` expires); for example,"
" in a separate dom0 terminal window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vm-troubleshooting.rst:14
#: b65166ac1f3947da9e23d449ee146be6
msgid ""
"In any case you can later access the VM’s logs (especially the VM console"
" log ``/var/log/xen/console/guest-VMNAME.log``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/troubleshooting/vm-troubleshooting.rst:16
#: fe14daeb524441d9963e962a524faa06
msgid ""
"You can always set the kernel back to some dom0-provided value to fix a "
"VM kernel installation."
msgstr ""

